stern Indochina:\n\nThe Chinese were energetically pushing construction of a motor road toward the northwestern corner of Tonkin in early 1953. The first 30 miles from Mengtze, the southern end of the Yunnan railroad, southwestward to the Red River were finished in February. Work is now in progress on the next section to Chinho (see map, p. 5).\n\nComment: This road construction which would enable the Chinese Communists to supply and support directly any future operation in Laos. At present the only motor road from Yunnan into Indochina runs from Mengtze to Lao Kay considerably east of this new road", "token_count": 107, "token_end_0based": 241, "token_start_0based": 135, "token_text": "3 chinese communists pushing new road toward northwestern indochina the chinese were energetically pushing construction of a motor road toward the northwestern corner of tonkin in early 1953 the first 30 miles from mengtze the southern end of the yunnan railroad southwestward to the red river were finished in february work is now in progress on the next section to chinho see map p 5 comment this road construction which would enable the chinese communists to supply and support directly any future operation in laos at present the only motor road from yunnan into indochina runs from mengtze to lao kay considerably east of this new road", "unred_source_page": 4}
